				\begin{document}$$dos(\varepsilon )=\,\frac{1}{V}\mathop{\sum }\limits_{i=1}^{N}\delta (\varepsilon -{\varepsilon }_{i}),$$\end{document}dos(ε)=1V∑i=1Nδ(ε−εi),where, δ(ε) is Dirac’s delta function. To scale the phonons to room temperature we account for the thermal expansion and replace V in Eq. (3) with the experimental room-temperature atomic volume for α-plutonium (20.0 Å3).
